overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application. The assistant first analyzed the existing implementation against
  the detailed specification, identifying several missing features and areas for
  improvement. Subsequently, the assistant proceeded to implement these changes.
  This included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with critical safety
  messaging, implementing detection and reporting for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia
  and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and incorporating a weighted
  scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). The CSV export
  functionality was enhanced to include all questionnaire responses, and new
  questions were added to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue symptoms.
  Placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health resources were
  also integrated into the generated reports. The process involved updating data
  types, validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic for both
  web and PDF outputs, with lint checks performed throughout the implementation.
